# EmbedFactory environment — TEMPLATE. Copy to .env (which is gitignored) and edit.

# =====================================================================================
# Reference documentation URLs
# =====================================================================================
# The mentor may consult these documentation sites (via WebFetch) to ground its help for
# tools/applications it has no local manual for — e.g. Flux.ai (PCB/EDA design).
#
# This is a SECURITY ALLOWLIST: the guard hook blocks any WebFetch whose URL does not begin
# with one of these prefixes. Add only documentation sites you trust. Comma-separated.
REFERENCE_DOC_URLS="https://docs.flux.ai/,https://docs.arduino.cc/,https://arduino.github.io/arduino-cli/"

# Optional named entries for readability (also keep each base URL in REFERENCE_DOC_URLS above):
FLUX_AI_DOCS="https://docs.flux.ai/"
# Arduino toolchains have no local IDE/CLI manual — these allowlisted doc roots let the mentor
# WebFetch the IDE, App Lab, and arduino-cli build/monitor/debug workflows:
ARDUINO_DOCS="https://docs.arduino.cc/"
ARDUINO_CLI_DOCS="https://arduino.github.io/arduino-cli/"
# Add more, e.g.:
# REFERENCE_DOC_URLS="https://docs.flux.ai/,https://docs.platformio.org/"
